!! $:/tags/ControlPanel/SettingsTab

The `controlpanel.tid` tiddler is tagged `$:/tags/ControlPanel/SettingsTab`, which makes it appear as a top-level tab in ControlPanel > Settings. TiddlyWiki's core ControlPanel uses `$list` with this tag to render settings tabs.

!! plugin-type[plugin] filter

The `plugin-type` field is set automatically by TiddlyWiki on all installed plugins. The hub uses this to discover rimir plugins without maintaining a manual list.

!! Shadow tiddler resolution

The hub checks for settings tiddlers using `[all[shadows+tiddlers]title<settingsTitle>]`. This searches both shadow tiddlers (bundled inside plugins) and real tiddlers (in the wiki store), ensuring the settings panel is found regardless of how the plugin delivers it.

!! $let widget

Used for computed CSS class assignment — the `isActive` variable compares the current iteration item against the stored selection state, and the `classes` variable concatenates the base class with the active modifier.

!! State tiddler pattern

`$:/state/rimir/core-hook/selected` follows TiddlyWiki's convention of using `$:/state/` prefix for UI state that is ephemeral and not synced to the server.

